cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with privacy-preserving outlier detection over encrypted datasets, which involves cryptography, data management, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DB (Databases), as the paper deals with data management and privacy concerns. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves algorithms and protocols, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
